  "instructions": [
    "Soak dried chickpeas in 4 cups cold water overnight, then drain.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add diced onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic and diced carrot; sauté for 2 minutes.",
    "Mix in tomato paste, cumin, and paprika until fragrant, 1 minute.",
    "Add canned tomatoes, vegetable broth, salt, and pepper; bring to a simmer.",
    "Return soaked chickpeas to the pot, cover, and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes, or until chickpeas are tender.",
    "Adjust seasoning and serve hot."
